The paper deals with algorithms for string similarity problems in the streaming model, which involves processing data in a single pass and with limited memory. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories related to data structures (cs.DS), algorithms and complexity (cs.CC), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper involves techniques for approximation and optimization, which could place it in the discrete mathematics (cs.DM) category.
